WEBVTT

00:00:01.400 --> 00:00:03.610
- A dispatcher?
- Yes.

00:00:03.610 --> 00:00:08.180
They're the people who answer 119 calls.

00:00:09.430 --> 00:00:13.180
I always think back to the person who answered my call

00:00:13.180 --> 00:00:17.420
when our house caught on fire.

00:00:17.420 --> 00:00:22.730
His voice was kind and resolute too.

00:00:22.730 --> 00:00:28.590
I like to think his voice saved us.

00:00:28.590 --> 00:00:36.050
So I want to be there for someone in their time of need as well.

00:00:38.960 --> 00:00:40.660
Onee-chan?

00:00:45.310 --> 00:00:49.060
Then what about your job at the bank?

00:00:49.060 --> 00:00:52.410
I'd have to resign and change careers, I guess.

00:00:52.410 --> 00:00:57.270
But first, I must be a certified firefighter to become a dispatcher.

00:00:57.270 --> 00:01:01.090
Who thought I'd be studying for an exam at my age?

00:01:01.090 --> 00:01:04.000
Certainly not me.

00:01:07.030 --> 00:01:10.650
Indeed. These look wonderful.

00:01:11.440 --> 00:01:16.630
I'll schedule another meeting when we further refine the design.

00:01:17.610 --> 00:01:20.440
[I'm sorry for the inconvenience I cause you with the meetings.]

00:01:20.440 --> 00:01:24.520
No worries at all. I'll reach out again.

00:01:25.720 --> 00:01:27.980
[Yes, talk to you again.]

00:01:35.150 --> 00:01:37.050
[Mom: Are you all right?]

00:01:46.100 --> 00:01:48.630
[Mom: Can I go through your things?]

00:01:52.060 --> 00:01:54.630
We've decided to renovate the second floor.
[Mom]

00:01:54.630 --> 00:01:59.730
Since your childhood bedroom is as is, can I go through your things?

00:02:05.530 --> 00:02:09.690
[Got it. I'll go do it myself in the coming days.]

00:02:14.820 --> 00:02:16.940
As Squad 2 has informed us,

00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:20.290
we are getting many calls for winter-related emergencies.

00:02:20.290 --> 00:02:22.610
- Let us be ready for that.
- Yes, Ma'am.

00:02:22.610 --> 00:02:26.160
Now, who hasn't gone for a checkup yet?

00:02:28.850 --> 00:02:30.920
I reckon you haven't either, Dojima-san.

00:02:30.920 --> 00:02:35.050
- I'll be fine.
- You're no exception, Sir.

00:02:35.050 --> 00:02:38.340
- Anyway, please schedule that as soon as possible.
- Yes, Ma'am.

00:02:38.340 --> 00:02:42.940
- Good morning.
- Morning.

00:02:42.940 --> 00:02:44.760
Allow me to introduce our newest dispatcher.

00:02:44.760 --> 00:02:48.700
This is Uesugi-kun. Starting today, he'll be joining our Squad 3.

00:02:48.700 --> 00:02:53.250
I'm Uesugi Subaru from Central Station. Pleased to meet you all.

00:02:53.250 --> 00:02:56.180
- The pleasure's ours.
- Now then, Tanaka-kun.

00:02:56.180 --> 00:03:02.160
Right. You are all aware of the "job rotation system"

00:03:02.160 --> 00:03:05.870
we plan to implement for Yokohama Fire, yes?

00:03:05.870 --> 00:03:08.300
By periodically shifting people's posts and duties,

00:03:08.300 --> 00:03:13.420
we hope to further strengthen the bonds of those at the Bureau.

00:03:13.420 --> 00:03:16.940
In other words, Minowa-kun, you'll be his mentor.

00:03:16.940 --> 00:03:18.090
- Pardon?
- What?

00:03:18.090 --> 00:03:20.620
But I completed my four days of training.

00:03:20.620 --> 00:03:23.670
Training never prepares you for the real deal.

00:03:23.670 --> 00:03:25.490
I see.

00:03:28.050 --> 00:03:30.750
All right, everyone. Let's get to today's work.

00:03:30.750 --> 00:03:34.100
Yes, Ma'am.

00:03:34.100 --> 00:03:38.740
- Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?
- A car hit a bike.

00:03:38.740 --> 00:03:40.630
The woman cycling was knocked into the road.

00:03:40.630 --> 00:03:42.240
- This is an accident?
- Yes.

00:03:42.240 --> 00:03:46.100
- May I get your location?
- Yokohama 305, He-12-something.

00:03:46.100 --> 00:03:47.700
That's all I remember.

00:03:47.700 --> 00:03:51.350
- Sir, is that a license plate number?
- Yes.

00:03:51.350 --> 00:03:54.090
The car drove off. Should I contact the police?

00:03:54.090 --> 00:03:58.720
We will contact them on our end. Can I first get an address?

00:03:58.720 --> 00:04:01.330
We'd like to send an ambulance right away.

00:04:01.330 --> 00:04:04.230
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:04:04.230 --> 00:04:06.330
I believe it'd be a medical emergency.

00:04:06.330 --> 00:04:07.570
What seems to be the matter?

00:04:07.570 --> 00:04:12.640
M-My mother. She tripped and hit her head as we left the house.

00:04:12.640 --> 00:04:16.340
She can't seem to move. Can we request an ambulance?

00:04:16.340 --> 00:04:20.550
Yes, Ma'am. Please tell us where to send the ambulance.

00:04:20.550 --> 00:04:22.320
[Receive call]

00:04:22.320 --> 00:04:25.100
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:04:25.100 --> 00:04:26.630
F-Fire!

00:04:26.630 --> 00:04:30.470
I was trying to fry some tempura when the whole pot went up in flames.

00:04:30.470 --> 00:04:32.070
Turning off the gas isn't helping either.

00:04:32.070 --> 00:04:34.500
Please tell us where to send our firefighters.

00:04:34.500 --> 00:04:36.950
5-20 Sasadocho, Kounan Ward.

00:04:36.950 --> 00:04:39.280
I have it here: 5-20 Sasadocho, Kounan Ward.

00:04:39.280 --> 00:04:42.390
- And whose residence is this?
- Mine, Morikawa.

00:04:42.390 --> 00:04:44.170
Morikawa-san, right?

00:04:44.170 --> 00:04:45.360
[Building Fire | Dispatch]

00:04:45.360 --> 00:04:49.310
I've sent our firefighters your way. Is your pot the only thing on fire?

00:04:49.310 --> 00:04:51.990
Y-Yes. Should I pour water on it?

00:04:51.990 --> 00:04:54.520
No, that would be extremely dangerous.

00:04:54.520 --> 00:04:56.290
Do you have a fire extinguisher on hand?

00:04:56.290 --> 00:04:59.110
- No, if I had one, I'd be using it!
- I see.

00:04:59.110 --> 00:05:02.400
- Uesugi-kun...
- Do you have a towel or spare bedsheet?

00:05:02.400 --> 00:05:05.400
- I have a towel.
- Run that towel under water,

00:05:05.400 --> 00:05:07.800
and wring it out.

00:05:07.800 --> 00:05:10.830
Sure. One moment.

00:05:10.830 --> 00:05:12.590
So like... this?

00:05:12.590 --> 00:05:15.040
Make sure the towel covers the whole pot.

00:05:15.040 --> 00:05:17.400
Once you've wrung it out, place it on the pot.

00:05:17.400 --> 00:05:19.740
I have the towel ready.

00:05:19.740 --> 00:05:23.310
Please cover the entire pot with that towel.

00:05:23.310 --> 00:05:25.070
I'll give it a try.

00:05:25.070 --> 00:05:27.580
Take care not to burn yourself.

00:05:28.290 --> 00:05:31.090
It's out. I think the fire's out.

00:05:31.090 --> 00:05:32.970
Please leave the towel there

00:05:32.970 --> 00:05:36.150
and wait for the firefighters somewhere away from the kitchen.

00:05:36.150 --> 00:05:38.170
I will. Thank you.

00:05:38.170 --> 00:05:40.420
Then I will be ending our call.

00:05:40.420 --> 00:05:43.210
- All right.
- Good bye.

00:05:47.980 --> 00:05:51.270
- Easy-peasy.
- Less work for me.

00:05:53.070 --> 00:05:56.640
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:05:57.350 --> 00:06:02.750
[119 Emergency Call]

00:06:02.750 --> 00:06:06.860
[CALL 6]

00:06:09.570 --> 00:06:13.000
- Bon appÃ©tit.
- Afternoon.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:15.340
- Hey.
- Hello there.

00:06:28.590 --> 00:06:30.570
All right!

00:06:30.570 --> 00:06:31.890
You really downed that.

00:06:31.890 --> 00:06:34.580
I must get this leg healed up, you know?

00:06:34.580 --> 00:06:37.380
See you both back at our stations.

00:06:41.720 --> 00:06:44.650
Could he at least drink his protein in peace?

00:06:44.650 --> 00:06:49.520
I admit that I was impressed with the way he handled that fire.

00:06:49.520 --> 00:06:52.710
I guess that's his area of expertise as a firefighter.

00:06:53.880 --> 00:06:55.940
You were impressed?

00:06:55.940 --> 00:06:57.350
Yes.

00:06:57.350 --> 00:07:00.050
That means you have a long way to go.

00:07:00.050 --> 00:07:01.460
Excuse me?

00:07:04.970 --> 00:07:07.570
- Good afternoon.
- Afternoon.

00:07:11.090 --> 00:07:12.250
Did you need something?

00:07:12.250 --> 00:07:15.180
That whole "job rotation" business...

00:07:15.180 --> 00:07:18.200
Is there something about it, Sir?

00:07:19.530 --> 00:07:21.650
Is it really as simple as that?

00:07:23.250 --> 00:07:25.440
Yes, Sir.

00:07:27.260 --> 00:07:29.240
Wh-What?

00:07:29.240 --> 00:07:31.420
W-Well, oh...

00:07:31.420 --> 00:07:33.250
You're a bit close.

00:07:36.450 --> 00:07:39.070
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:07:39.070 --> 00:07:41.480
So, the fire department...

00:07:41.480 --> 00:07:45.010
- Yes?
- Your radio communication is digital now, right?

00:07:45.010 --> 00:07:47.030
Why did you change that?

00:07:47.030 --> 00:07:50.420
- Pardon?
- Can you guys go back to analog?

00:07:50.420 --> 00:07:54.890
I really liked listening to your communication. I listened all the time.

00:07:54.890 --> 00:07:59.590
I always anticipated hearing those voices, but thenâ€”

00:07:59.590 --> 00:08:00.680
- H-Hello?
- Can I hang up?

00:08:00.680 --> 00:08:03.040
- Hear him out a bit longer, all right?
- Hello?

00:08:03.040 --> 00:08:06.480
You guys went digital. I haven't heard those voices in a decade.

00:08:06.480 --> 00:08:09.560
- I miss it, really!
- What an oddball.

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:13.450
I understand you made the change to prevent leaking personal information, but...

00:08:13.450 --> 00:08:15.390
Sir, this is a line for emergencies.

00:08:15.390 --> 00:08:17.370
I will be hanging up if there is none.

00:08:17.370 --> 00:08:20.540
- H-Hey, I haven't...
- Have a good one.

00:08:20.540 --> 00:08:23.510
Your first junk call. Congrats.

00:08:23.510 --> 00:08:25.270
You deal with these every day?

00:08:25.270 --> 00:08:26.810
Not "every"...

00:08:26.810 --> 00:08:28.500
No, you're right. Every day.
[Prank]

00:08:28.500 --> 00:08:30.100
Doesn't that get annoying?

00:08:30.100 --> 00:08:34.920
If every call were an emergency, that'd be exhausting in its own right.

00:08:34.920 --> 00:08:37.580
Having nothing wrong is best.

00:08:37.580 --> 00:08:39.430
Seems you get to take it easy.

00:08:39.430 --> 00:08:41.430
I wouldn't say that.

00:08:42.550 --> 00:08:45.160
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:08:45.160 --> 00:08:47.280
It's Misono! I need an ambulance!

00:08:47.280 --> 00:08:51.090
My right leg hurts, and I can't walk!

00:08:51.090 --> 00:08:52.830
Misono-san, right?

00:08:52.830 --> 00:08:55.310
- Where are you now?
- That must be Misotatsu-san.

00:08:55.310 --> 00:08:58.470
You know where. The crosswalk on Yamashita Bridge!

00:08:58.470 --> 00:09:02.030
I tried to cross the dang thing when my leg started hurting again.

00:09:02.030 --> 00:09:04.190
The crossing at Yamashita Bridge, yes?

00:09:04.190 --> 00:09:05.830
Oh, Misotatsu-san again?

00:09:05.830 --> 00:09:08.150
- "Misotatsu"?
- Misono Tatsuo-san.

00:09:08.150 --> 00:09:10.800
He's a frequent caller of ours.

00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:13.440
So, he calls often?

00:09:13.440 --> 00:09:18.800
Yes, and it's always because he can't move at the crossing on Yamashita Bridge.

00:09:18.800 --> 00:09:21.800
If he claims he can't move, we must send an ambulance.

00:09:21.800 --> 00:09:24.330
But he perks up and leaves once paramedics arrive.

00:09:24.330 --> 00:09:26.130
Don't send an ambulance to a guy like him.

00:09:26.130 --> 00:09:29.220
If we don't, he doesn't budge.

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:30.960
And the pain isn't receding?

00:09:30.960 --> 00:09:32.670
No, not at all!

00:09:32.670 --> 00:09:37.970
Ouch! I can't move. I'll be hit by a car!
[Risk Assessment]

00:09:37.970 --> 00:09:39.820
I've sent an ambulance your way.
[Dispatch]

00:09:39.820 --> 00:09:43.270
Really? Great, I'll be waiting.

00:09:45.140 --> 00:09:49.030
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:09:51.800 --> 00:09:55.750
Hello? This is the Yokohama Fire Bureau, 119.

00:09:55.750 --> 00:09:58.760
Do you require assistance with a fire or an ambulance?

00:09:58.760 --> 00:10:02.900
- An ambulance.
- All right.

00:10:02.900 --> 00:10:08.120
But I don't need one now. Could you come in thirty minutes?

00:10:09.630 --> 00:10:14.250
I'm sorry, but we can't send our ambulances on a delay.

00:10:14.250 --> 00:10:17.260
Do you not require aid immediately?
[Listen In]

00:10:17.260 --> 00:10:21.910
I... I'm planning on dying now.

00:10:21.910 --> 00:10:23.180
What?

00:10:23.180 --> 00:10:29.250
But I don't want my mom to be the first to find my body, so...

00:10:29.250 --> 00:10:32.220
F-For now, let's calm down, okay?

00:10:32.220 --> 00:10:34.520
Ending your life is...

00:10:34.520 --> 00:10:38.540
I don't want to be here anymore.

00:10:38.540 --> 00:10:40.310
There's no point.

00:10:40.310 --> 00:10:42.550
I see...

00:10:42.550 --> 00:10:46.590
Oh, well...

00:10:46.590 --> 00:10:49.040
Where are you right now?

00:10:49.040 --> 00:10:52.530
In my bathtub.

00:10:52.530 --> 00:10:54.280
So you are home.

00:10:54.280 --> 00:10:57.780
In that case, could I please get your address?

00:10:57.780 --> 00:10:59.480
Kasuhara, not yet.

00:10:59.480 --> 00:11:05.300
- What?
- Room 403, 4-7 Yuunagicho, Isogo Ward.

00:11:05.300 --> 00:11:07.920
Promise me you'll come, okay?

00:11:07.920 --> 00:11:11.450
- I'll end things on my end, too.
- No, wait!

00:11:11.450 --> 00:11:14.470
- I get it now, I...
- Call her back.

00:11:14.470 --> 00:11:16.720
Yes, Sir.
[Return Call]

00:11:26.960 --> 00:11:28.780
Send out the Isogo paramedics.
[Central Control]

00:11:28.780 --> 00:11:31.440
Their sirens could push her to act.

00:11:31.440 --> 00:11:33.360
Have them informed of every update we get.

00:11:33.360 --> 00:11:34.720
All right.
[Dispatch]

00:11:34.720 --> 00:11:37.450
The number you have called is...

00:11:37.450 --> 00:11:38.790
This is the Isogo paramedic squad.

00:11:38.790 --> 00:11:40.370
[Calling]

00:11:40.370 --> 00:11:42.960
- We have lost contact with the individual.
- Please... pick up.

00:11:42.960 --> 00:11:45.840
We have no read on the current situation.

00:11:45.840 --> 00:11:47.610
Understood.

00:11:47.610 --> 00:11:52.280
Kasuhara, when she picks up, prioritize calming her down.

00:11:52.280 --> 00:11:53.870
Yes, Sir.

00:11:57.220 --> 00:11:58.290
Hello?

00:11:58.290 --> 00:12:01.670
It's me, the lady from the Fire Bureau you spoke to earlier.

00:12:01.670 --> 00:12:03.710
Right now, are you...

00:12:04.480 --> 00:12:06.280
No, I mean.

00:12:06.280 --> 00:12:07.930
I...

00:12:09.620 --> 00:12:11.560
I'm sorry.

00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:13.060
Pardon?

00:12:13.060 --> 00:12:17.970
Earlier, I kept asking questions

00:12:17.970 --> 00:12:21.980
without listening to your side of the story.

00:12:22.830 --> 00:12:24.960
If you wouldn't mind,

00:12:26.090 --> 00:12:29.170
could you please tell me more about yourself?

00:12:30.360 --> 00:12:32.580
I'll be here to listen.

00:12:37.120 --> 00:12:39.470
This is Yokohama Fire. We copy that.

00:12:39.470 --> 00:12:43.060
Misotatsu-san walked home without taking the ambulance.

00:12:43.060 --> 00:12:44.730
Understood.

00:12:44.730 --> 00:12:47.020
Geez, seriously?

00:12:47.020 --> 00:12:52.920
You don't have to force yourself to speak if you're not up to it.

00:12:52.920 --> 00:12:57.260
But I'll continue this call, just in case.

00:12:58.230 --> 00:13:02.640
Ma'am, I'm okay now.

00:13:02.640 --> 00:13:07.110
Your call has calmed me down.

00:13:08.230 --> 00:13:09.620
Really?

00:13:09.620 --> 00:13:11.750
Yes.

00:13:11.750 --> 00:13:15.780
I won't need an ambulance anymore.

00:13:23.110 --> 00:13:24.840
Okay.

00:13:24.840 --> 00:13:29.620
Just call us again if anything happens, okay?

00:13:29.620 --> 00:13:31.050
I will.

00:13:31.050 --> 00:13:34.640
Then I'll end our call here.

00:13:35.530 --> 00:13:38.810
Is it really our job to handle such things?

00:13:47.560 --> 00:13:50.440
Was that your first call from someone contemplating suicide?

00:13:51.380 --> 00:13:53.190
Yes, Ma'am.

00:13:53.190 --> 00:13:55.400
I panicked.

00:13:55.400 --> 00:13:59.840
All I could think about was locating her.

00:14:01.690 --> 00:14:05.380
If I had been more levelheaded about the situation...

00:14:06.700 --> 00:14:10.680
But you were able to prevent the worst from happening.

00:14:10.680 --> 00:14:13.590
Those results are far more important

00:14:13.590 --> 00:14:16.280
than any fruitless chase you send paramedics on.

00:14:17.580 --> 00:14:20.390
Remember, sympathizing with our callers

00:14:20.390 --> 00:14:22.990
is essential in this line of work.

00:14:23.830 --> 00:14:25.290
Yes, Ma'am.

00:14:44.100 --> 00:14:46.360
What are you so upset about?

00:14:47.820 --> 00:14:51.590
You send our paramedics out for the most inane calls.

00:14:51.590 --> 00:14:55.150
I didn't realize counseling was part of the job too.

00:14:56.050 --> 00:14:59.800
If the caller needs that support, we give it.

00:14:59.800 --> 00:15:01.540
You must be joking.

00:15:01.540 --> 00:15:04.220
So you'll act all sympathetic, too?

00:15:05.260 --> 00:15:07.670
If you humor every last call, you'll see no end to it.

00:15:07.670 --> 00:15:10.970
You have to assert yourself.

00:15:10.970 --> 00:15:15.110
You have to express care when listening to people.

00:15:15.110 --> 00:15:17.260
"Express care"?

00:15:20.940 --> 00:15:23.730
This job's hard because things aren't so clear cut.

00:15:23.730 --> 00:15:29.760
A method that works for one caller may not fly for another.

00:15:30.810 --> 00:15:33.990
There's no right answer for dealing with these calls.

00:15:34.780 --> 00:15:38.370
So you're dispatching our squads with that indecisive attitude?

00:15:38.370 --> 00:15:41.090
I don't get it.

00:15:45.000 --> 00:15:48.280
- Please tell us where to send the ambulance.
- I understand.

00:15:48.280 --> 00:15:49.820
I see.

00:15:49.820 --> 00:15:51.850
- Your abdomen is in pain.
- Yes.

00:15:51.850 --> 00:15:53.010
Yes.

00:15:53.010 --> 00:15:54.510
When did the pain begin?

00:15:54.510 --> 00:16:00.340
Two hours ago. But I haven't been able to push any out in a week.

00:16:00.340 --> 00:16:02.490
Push out what, Sir?

00:16:02.490 --> 00:16:06.320
You know, a really big one...

00:16:06.320 --> 00:16:07.260
[Muted]

00:16:07.260 --> 00:16:09.290
Sir, this guy is just constipated.

00:16:09.290 --> 00:16:12.260
Being constipated for a week is no joke.

00:16:12.260 --> 00:16:14.450
Continue the call.

00:16:14.450 --> 00:16:16.620
Will you be needing an ambulance?

00:16:16.620 --> 00:16:21.920
Y-Yes, please! I-I've never felt this much pain before...

00:16:22.810 --> 00:16:24.530
Let's send him one.

00:16:25.790 --> 00:16:29.220
We will send an ambulance your way. May I have an address please?

00:16:29.220 --> 00:16:30.850
An address? Right.

00:16:30.850 --> 00:16:35.220
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:16:35.220 --> 00:16:41.180
It hurts. Wh-What do I do?

00:16:41.180 --> 00:16:43.230
What seems to be the matter?

00:16:43.230 --> 00:16:46.080
Ma'am, remain calm.
[Breathing...]

00:16:46.080 --> 00:16:48.940
My heart is beating so fast. Am I...

00:16:50.710 --> 00:16:55.170
Ma'am, remain calm. Do you know your current location?

00:16:55.850 --> 00:16:57.920
[Listen In]

00:16:57.920 --> 00:17:00.030
Are there any landmarks, or...

00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:07.450
Ma'am, let's take some deep breaths.

00:17:08.310 --> 00:17:10.280
O-Okay.

00:17:11.170 --> 00:17:13.420
Slowly breathe in...

00:17:14.800 --> 00:17:17.320
And breathe out.

00:17:21.000 --> 00:17:22.950
You're doing great.

00:17:22.950 --> 00:17:25.710
When you're able to speak,

00:17:25.710 --> 00:17:32.400
may I get your name and age?

00:17:32.400 --> 00:17:36.840
Yes. My name is Koda.

00:17:40.100 --> 00:17:45.400
Koda-san, it's okay. I'm right here with you.

00:17:45.400 --> 00:17:47.820
I will send an ambulance your way.

00:17:47.820 --> 00:17:51.070
Do you know where you are?

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:56.190
Th-This is my first time in Yokohama.

00:17:56.190 --> 00:17:59.660
I came for an interview.

00:17:59.660 --> 00:18:01.530
Let's figure out where you are together.

00:18:01.530 --> 00:18:04.810
Don't worry, I'm in no rush.

00:18:05.880 --> 00:18:10.010
O-Okay, I'd appreciate that.

00:18:18.700 --> 00:18:20.290
[Pedestrians and bicycles only]

00:18:40.770 --> 00:18:43.340
[7-5-1 Minatomirai, Nishi Ward]

00:18:43.340 --> 00:18:44.990
This is it.

00:19:09.440 --> 00:19:13.170
It hurts. Wh-What do I do?

00:19:14.860 --> 00:19:20.160
Koda-san, it's okay. I'm right here with you.

00:19:20.160 --> 00:19:22.550
I will send an ambulance your way.

00:19:22.550 --> 00:19:24.550
Do you know where you are?

00:19:24.550 --> 00:19:29.350
Th-This is my first time in Yokohama.

00:19:29.350 --> 00:19:32.300
I-I came for an interview.

00:19:32.300 --> 00:19:37.450
She was in a new place, surrounded by other interviewees.

00:19:37.450 --> 00:19:40.380
She must have been incredibly anxious.

00:19:47.650 --> 00:19:51.850
Sympathizing with people is easier said than done.

00:19:57.760 --> 00:19:59.460
What?

00:19:59.460 --> 00:20:02.850
Your sister says she's coming home today.

00:20:19.770 --> 00:20:23.820
- Look what I found.
- Oh, my.

00:20:23.820 --> 00:20:25.100
How nostalgic.

00:20:25.100 --> 00:20:28.510
- You remember when she drew this, right?
- Of course.

00:20:34.800 --> 00:20:37.640
- Welcome home.
- Welcome home!

00:21:37.070 --> 00:21:39.630
Did you finish sorting through your room?

00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:44.940
You'll be eating dinner with us, right?

00:21:51.400 --> 00:21:54.750
I'm home. Is Onee-chan back already?

00:21:55.510 --> 00:21:59.760
We haven't had family dinner in a while. I thought it'd be nice.

00:22:00.680 --> 00:22:02.460
Onee-chan!

00:22:15.380 --> 00:22:18.900
[I have a deadline today. I'll be heading out.]

00:22:21.390 --> 00:22:23.370
I see.

00:22:24.900 --> 00:22:27.160
Wait, before you go!

00:22:33.150 --> 00:22:35.440
Make sure you eat well, okay?

00:22:39.510 --> 00:22:41.580
Take care now.

00:22:44.510 --> 00:22:49.620
I thought we could have a family dinner with all four of us.

00:22:49.620 --> 00:22:53.620
She looked busy. Nothing we can do about that.

00:22:55.060 --> 00:22:58.040
And how about you, Yuki?

00:22:58.040 --> 00:23:00.570
Is work going well?

00:23:01.630 --> 00:23:06.040
I'm not sure, but I'm certainly doing my best.

00:23:06.040 --> 00:23:08.940
I'm blessed with great Senpais and supervisors.

00:23:08.940 --> 00:23:11.290
That's good to hear.

00:23:11.290 --> 00:23:14.580
- This was the job you wanted to pursue, after all.
- True.

00:23:15.900 --> 00:23:22.270
I wanted to tell Onee-chan that I am doing well...

00:23:23.920 --> 00:23:28.850
I'm sure you're busy, but be sure to visit every now and then, all right?

00:23:28.850 --> 00:23:30.940
I will.

00:23:30.940 --> 00:23:33.320
We could've just talked over the phone.

00:23:33.320 --> 00:23:35.340
You want to ask about Uesugi, right?

00:23:35.340 --> 00:23:37.850
I heard from a guy in General Affairs.

00:23:37.850 --> 00:23:41.130
You're the one who pushed him to the Command Center, Iida. Why?

00:23:43.930 --> 00:23:47.580
Uesugi's been on my squad for two years now.

00:23:47.580 --> 00:23:50.060
It's great that he takes action during an emergency,

00:23:50.060 --> 00:23:53.530
but it's like he's gotten too used to it.

00:23:53.530 --> 00:23:55.630
- You can tell, right?
- Yes.

00:23:55.630 --> 00:23:58.710
It's a dangerous rookie mindset to have.

00:23:59.400 --> 00:24:03.240
He needs to learn that those on the frontlines

00:24:03.240 --> 00:24:05.410
aren't the only stars of the show.

00:24:06.480 --> 00:24:09.430
Your two draft beers.

00:24:09.430 --> 00:24:11.700
Enjoy.

00:24:11.700 --> 00:24:13.300
Cheers.

00:24:20.290 --> 00:24:23.850
So, how do you feel as the pioneer?

00:24:23.850 --> 00:24:25.840
- Of what?
- This job rotation business.

00:24:25.840 --> 00:24:28.970
I'm not on rotation.

00:24:30.470 --> 00:24:33.390
You don't feel like returning to the squad?

00:24:35.020 --> 00:24:38.540
It's not a matter of whether I feel like returning or not.

00:24:40.240 --> 00:24:43.660
So that incident still gets to you.

00:24:43.660 --> 00:24:46.370
That accident wasn't your fault, all right?

00:24:54.760 --> 00:24:58.080
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:24:58.080 --> 00:25:00.890
A medical emergency...

00:25:00.890 --> 00:25:02.460
What seems to be the matter?

00:25:02.460 --> 00:25:04.810
I'm at work, and my boss was...

00:25:04.810 --> 00:25:07.990
What happened to your boss, Sir?

00:25:07.990 --> 00:25:09.990
Th-There's blood...

00:25:09.990 --> 00:25:14.440
So he's bleeding, yes? And where is he bleeding from?

00:25:14.440 --> 00:25:17.030
H-His chest.

00:25:17.030 --> 00:25:18.780
"His chest"? He's bleeding from his chest?

00:25:18.780 --> 00:25:20.420
Yes.

00:25:20.420 --> 00:25:23.930
Do you know why he's bleeding from his chest?

00:25:26.010 --> 00:25:29.880
Hello, Sir? Could you please tell us what's going on?

00:25:29.880 --> 00:25:32.300
- He was...
- Pardon?

00:25:32.300 --> 00:25:35.260
He was stabbed.

00:25:35.260 --> 00:25:38.180
- What?
- He's calling from Minami-no-Dai, Totsuka Ward.

00:25:38.180 --> 00:25:39.710
- Contact the police.
- Yes, Ma'am.

00:25:39.710 --> 00:25:41.350
He was stabbed?

00:25:41.350 --> 00:25:43.960
Your boss was stabbed in the chest?

00:25:43.960 --> 00:25:46.010
Calm down. First, make sure the caller is safe.

00:25:46.010 --> 00:25:48.860
Is he conscious? Do you know if he's conscious or not?

00:25:48.860 --> 00:25:52.520
And could you tell me your address?

00:25:52.520 --> 00:25:54.140
No, I...

00:25:54.140 --> 00:25:57.230
Then the company's name. You know that much, right?

00:25:57.230 --> 00:25:59.160
- Well...
- Uesugi, he might not be able to speak.

00:25:59.160 --> 00:26:01.680
Why don't you know? He was stabbed, right?

00:26:01.680 --> 00:26:04.680
We need to send him an ambulance now!

00:26:04.680 --> 00:26:06.880
I'll take over from here.

00:26:15.820 --> 00:26:17.480
Sir, I will be handling your call.

00:26:17.480 --> 00:26:20.300
There are several questions I'd like to ask.

00:26:20.300 --> 00:26:26.070
You may respond with a simple "yes" or "no."

00:26:26.070 --> 00:26:31.650
If that is also risky, a "yay" or "nay" will also work.

00:26:31.650 --> 00:26:36.620
Is the individual who stabbed your boss still in the vicinity?

00:26:36.620 --> 00:26:38.200
Yay.

00:26:39.060 --> 00:26:44.010
Are you, the caller, currently in a safe location?

00:26:44.010 --> 00:26:46.090
Nay.

00:26:46.090 --> 00:26:49.470
- The perpetrator is nearby?
- Yes.

00:26:50.260 --> 00:26:53.580
Can you move to safety?

00:26:53.580 --> 00:26:54.810
No.

00:26:54.810 --> 00:26:56.960
Damn it...

00:26:59.080 --> 00:27:00.760
I have a couple more questions.

00:27:00.760 --> 00:27:03.990
Your boss is a man, correct?

00:27:03.990 --> 00:27:05.360
Yes.

00:27:05.360 --> 00:27:08.050
Is he still conscious?

00:27:08.050 --> 00:27:09.850
No...

00:27:12.000 --> 00:27:13.690
Dojima-san.

00:27:14.470 --> 00:27:15.830
These are stores in that area.

00:27:15.830 --> 00:27:19.130
From first to last, there's an eatery, pharmacy, and used car dealership.

00:27:19.130 --> 00:27:21.840
[Yoi no Toki Eatery, Daio Pharmacy, S and Company Dealership]

00:27:24.170 --> 00:27:27.720
Is your establishment a used car dealership, Sir?

00:27:27.720 --> 00:27:31.620
- Yes.
- "S and Company," perhaps?

00:27:31.620 --> 00:27:33.100
Yeah!

00:27:33.100 --> 00:27:34.770
[S and Company]

00:27:34.770 --> 00:27:36.840
Understood.

00:27:36.840 --> 00:27:41.450
I'm sending an ambulance and some police your way.

00:27:41.450 --> 00:27:43.930
You may either stay on this line

00:27:43.930 --> 00:27:48.150
or hang up if you feel you are in danger.

00:27:48.150 --> 00:27:50.110
Okay.

00:27:50.110 --> 00:27:52.090
The caller is still in immediate danger.

00:27:52.090 --> 00:27:56.040
Please be wary when approaching the facility.

00:27:59.400 --> 00:28:01.270
We'll probably get questions from the press.

00:28:01.270 --> 00:28:03.610
I'll let General Affairs know.

00:28:05.660 --> 00:28:09.370
That was a difficult case. I don't blame you.

00:28:15.680 --> 00:28:18.230
An employee of the used car dealership "S and Company"

00:28:18.230 --> 00:28:21.790
- called 119 at 5:30 a.m.,
- Oh, there's the news.

00:28:21.790 --> 00:28:25.670
reporting that his boss had been stabbed in the chest.

00:28:25.670 --> 00:28:29.380
The suspect was soon arrested at the scene of the crime.

00:28:29.380 --> 00:28:31.870
The victim, Chief Shikata Yoshinori,

00:28:31.870 --> 00:28:34.180
was transported to a hospital,

00:28:34.180 --> 00:28:36.840
but he unfortunately lost his life.

00:28:36.840 --> 00:28:40.680
Though the dealership was open and several staff were present,

00:28:40.680 --> 00:28:43.810
there were no other casualties or injuries.

00:28:43.810 --> 00:28:49.120
Police are currently looking into possible motives, and...

00:28:49.120 --> 00:28:52.760
Do you know the scariest part of this job?

00:28:55.670 --> 00:28:57.730
Giving in to self-conceit.

00:28:58.550 --> 00:29:00.470
"Self-conceit"?

00:29:00.470 --> 00:29:03.600
No matter how experienced or used to this you are,

00:29:03.600 --> 00:29:06.960
no two calls can be handled the same.

00:29:06.960 --> 00:29:10.830
Knowing that and actually understanding makes all the difference.

00:29:33.230 --> 00:29:37.170
I'm sorry for my actions earlier, Sir.

00:29:37.980 --> 00:29:39.900
Uesugi.

00:29:40.880 --> 00:29:45.500
You underestimate human beings.

00:29:45.500 --> 00:29:47.120
Pardon?

00:29:47.120 --> 00:29:51.860
Getting a hundred calls means a hundred unique individuals are seeking help.

00:29:51.860 --> 00:29:55.920
You've only lived twenty-some years.

00:29:55.920 --> 00:29:58.790
You can't handle each of those cases perfectly.

00:30:00.070 --> 00:30:01.280
Yes, Sir.

00:30:01.280 --> 00:30:07.360
I've lived a little over sixty years and still get caught off guard.

00:30:08.740 --> 00:30:10.900
Then what should I do?

00:30:12.510 --> 00:30:14.980
You listen.

00:30:15.690 --> 00:30:18.230
Listen to the caller's voice

00:30:18.230 --> 00:30:20.100
and surrounding sounds.

00:30:20.100 --> 00:30:24.370
You imagine the situation they're in

00:30:24.370 --> 00:30:27.340
and find the best words to say,

00:30:28.130 --> 00:30:31.090
all while praying you've made the right move.

00:30:32.510 --> 00:30:38.860
Repeat that cycle and hone your dispatching skills.

00:30:38.860 --> 00:30:41.070
That's really all you can do.

00:30:45.920 --> 00:30:47.760
Sleep when you can, okay?

00:30:47.760 --> 00:30:49.910
These nights tend to get long.

00:30:57.220 --> 00:31:01.760
[1:05 a.m.]

00:31:17.800 --> 00:31:20.300
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:31:20.300 --> 00:31:23.130
Can I talk to a woman?

00:31:24.100 --> 00:31:27.170
[Transferring]

00:31:27.170 --> 00:31:28.400
[Connected]

00:31:28.400 --> 00:31:30.440
Hello, what seems to be the issue?

00:31:30.440 --> 00:31:32.710
I was hit by a man.

00:31:32.710 --> 00:31:35.250
And I'm bleeding from my face.

00:31:35.250 --> 00:31:37.390
Where should I send an ambulance?

00:31:37.390 --> 00:31:40.110
Where? I'm busy running away!

00:31:40.110 --> 00:31:43.590
So you're outside, running from the man who hit you?

00:31:43.590 --> 00:31:46.440
Yes, from a guy who calls himself my ex.

00:31:46.440 --> 00:31:48.680
"Calls himself your ex"...

00:31:48.680 --> 00:31:50.310
Where'd you go?

00:31:50.310 --> 00:31:51.950
Oh no, he's close!

00:31:51.950 --> 00:31:55.420
He started throwing punches after I rejected him.

00:31:55.420 --> 00:31:59.360
What sort of 38-year-old asks out a teen? He's insane!

00:31:59.360 --> 00:32:00.750
Have you called the police?

00:32:00.750 --> 00:32:04.150
No, no way. I ran away from home!

00:32:04.150 --> 00:32:05.520
Got it.

00:32:05.520 --> 00:32:08.090
So you want to take an ambulance to the hospital.

00:32:08.090 --> 00:32:10.080
Are you still running?

00:32:10.080 --> 00:32:13.370
I don't have an address, but I'm hiding between a small shop

00:32:13.370 --> 00:32:17.060
and hardware store near Yamashita Park.

00:32:17.060 --> 00:32:18.860
I think that dude is nearby, too.

00:32:18.860 --> 00:32:21.520
Meaning he'd find you if we send an ambulance...

00:32:21.520 --> 00:32:24.270
Can't you turn off the siren or something?

00:32:24.270 --> 00:32:26.380
We actually can't.

00:32:26.380 --> 00:32:28.990
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:32:28.990 --> 00:32:32.580
Oh, ouch! I can't walk!

00:32:32.580 --> 00:32:36.260
Send an ambulance right away!

00:32:36.260 --> 00:32:38.470
Did you perhaps call us earlier, Sir?

00:32:38.470 --> 00:32:41.700
Yes, it's me, Misono. Now hurry!

00:32:41.700 --> 00:32:43.410
Understood, Misono-san.

00:32:43.410 --> 00:32:47.220
- Misotatsu has the worst timing.
- Are you currently outdoors?

00:32:47.220 --> 00:32:48.730
Of course, I am!

00:32:48.730 --> 00:32:53.280
I wanted to go enjoy the night breeze, but now I can't move!

00:32:53.280 --> 00:32:55.570
May I ask where you are?

00:32:55.570 --> 00:32:57.930
I'm at my usual crossing!

00:32:57.930 --> 00:33:01.570
- The one at Yamashita Bridge, in Naka Ward.
- Got it.

00:33:01.570 --> 00:33:03.670
I will send an ambulance your way.

00:33:03.670 --> 00:33:06.430
Please wait and remain safe.

00:33:06.430 --> 00:33:09.040
Will do. Appreciate it!

00:33:09.040 --> 00:33:10.460
Of course.
[Dispatch]

00:33:11.570 --> 00:33:14.050
I wonder if he'll walk away again.

00:33:14.050 --> 00:33:19.080
Hold on. Misotatsu-san calls for an ambulance along Yamashita Bridge, right?

00:33:19.080 --> 00:33:20.690
Yes.

00:33:20.690 --> 00:33:22.200
I've already dispatched a squad his way.

00:33:22.200 --> 00:33:26.060
Yamashita Bridge is right by Marine Tower.

00:33:28.570 --> 00:33:31.860
Say, do you know where Yokohama Marine Tower is?

00:33:31.860 --> 00:33:34.680
Yes, I think I'm nearby.

00:33:34.680 --> 00:33:37.790
- There's going to be an ambulance headed that way.
- What?

00:33:37.790 --> 00:33:40.430
So how about it? Can you run?

00:33:40.430 --> 00:33:41.910
Yes, I think so.

00:33:41.910 --> 00:33:44.580
Then run toward Marine Tower.

00:33:44.580 --> 00:33:46.030
Okay.

00:33:50.040 --> 00:33:52.850
Tell me when you start to hear a siren.

00:33:57.000 --> 00:33:59.150
No way, I hear it!

00:33:59.150 --> 00:34:02.130
It's close!

00:34:02.130 --> 00:34:04.060
Fire department's 119.

00:34:04.060 --> 00:34:06.360
- Am I speaking to Misono-san?
- Yes.

00:34:06.360 --> 00:34:09.190
- Sir, the ambulance is about to arrive.
- Sorry!

00:34:09.190 --> 00:34:11.990
I'm not hurting anymore, so I'll head home.

00:34:11.990 --> 00:34:14.610
Feel free to call off the ambulance.

00:34:14.610 --> 00:34:17.860
Is that so? I understand.

00:34:23.380 --> 00:34:26.000
Central Paramedic, this is Yokohama Fire Bureau.

00:34:26.000 --> 00:34:27.110
A girl is headed your way.

00:34:27.110 --> 00:34:30.860
Please take her to the nearest hospital when she arrives.

00:34:30.860 --> 00:34:32.440
Copy that.

00:34:33.860 --> 00:34:36.170
I see it! I see the ambulance!

00:34:36.170 --> 00:34:38.840
Go ahead and run on in.

00:34:38.840 --> 00:34:40.740
Come onboard.

00:34:45.220 --> 00:34:47.510
I'm in! I'm in the ambulance!

00:34:47.510 --> 00:34:50.120
Holy cow, I've never been in an ambulance before!

00:34:50.120 --> 00:34:52.230
I'm glad you made it. Take care, okay?

00:34:52.230 --> 00:34:57.060
Thank you, Onee-san! I'll never forget what you did for me today!

00:34:57.060 --> 00:35:00.030
- Then I'll go ahead and end this call.
- Okay!

00:35:04.800 --> 00:35:06.910
That was amazing, Team Leader.

00:35:06.910 --> 00:35:09.710
I didn't even know that was allowed.

00:35:09.710 --> 00:35:11.310
I'm surprised it worked out.

00:35:11.310 --> 00:35:13.910
Honestly, I thought we were done for.

00:35:13.910 --> 00:35:15.780
It's amazing.

00:35:48.020 --> 00:35:51.170
I'm sorry for my attitude yesterday.

00:35:51.170 --> 00:35:53.520
I look forward to learning more today.

00:36:05.590 --> 00:36:08.930
Not to worry, we've sent an ambulance your way.

00:36:08.930 --> 00:36:11.570
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:36:11.570 --> 00:36:16.790
It's my husband. We're currently home, and he says his stomach hurts.

00:36:16.790 --> 00:36:18.370
He's drenched in sweat as well.

00:36:18.370 --> 00:36:20.350
I understand.

00:36:20.350 --> 00:36:22.720
May I get your name and an address, please?

00:36:22.720 --> 00:36:26.580
Oh, but my husband has locked himself in our bathroom

00:36:26.580 --> 00:36:28.690
and insists he doesn't need an ambulance.

00:36:28.690 --> 00:36:32.490
I see. If your husband refuses an ambulance,

00:36:32.490 --> 00:36:35.210
we can't force him to take one.

00:36:35.210 --> 00:36:38.710
Right, I had assumed.

00:36:39.870 --> 00:36:44.020
If you're worried, would you like me to speak to your husband directly?

00:36:44.020 --> 00:36:46.500
No, no need to trouble yourself.

00:36:46.500 --> 00:36:49.650
- Are you sure? Just to be safe...
- No need to push them.

00:36:49.650 --> 00:36:53.020
They'll call again if they really need our assistance.

00:36:53.020 --> 00:36:56.500
Okay. Then I will not send an ambulance.

00:36:56.500 --> 00:36:58.950
But please don't hesitate to call 119 again.

00:36:58.950 --> 00:37:03.000
- I won't.
- I will be ending this call.

00:37:03.000 --> 00:37:04.520
All right.

00:37:07.120 --> 00:37:10.280
Fire department's 119. Is it a fire or medical emergency?

00:37:10.280 --> 00:37:13.170
- Well, excuse me, we're in a taxi now.
- I see.

00:37:13.170 --> 00:37:15.450
M-My wife... It seems her water broke.

00:37:15.450 --> 00:37:16.650
Understood.

00:37:16.650 --> 00:37:19.490
Could I please get your wife's age and your name, Sir?

00:37:19.490 --> 00:37:23.380
I'm Imai. My wife is 38.

00:37:23.380 --> 00:37:25.060
Imai-san, right?

00:37:25.060 --> 00:37:26.990
How many weeks along is your wife?

